President Donald J. Trump has declared a major disaster in the State of Iowa due to severe storms and tornadoes that occurred on July 19, 2018. Federal assistance will be provided to supplement State and local recovery efforts in the affected areas. The counties of Lee, Marion, Marshall, and Van Buren are eligible for federal funding on a cost-sharing basis for emergency work and the repair or replacement of damaged facilities. Hazard mitigation measures statewide are also eligible for federal funding on a cost-sharing basis. Timothy J. Scranton has been named the Federal Coordinating Officer for Federal recovery operations in the affected areas. Further damage assessments may lead to additional designations at a later date if requested by the State. For more information, contact the FEMA News Desk at (202) 646-3272 or FEMA-NEWS-DESK@FEMA.DHS.GOV.